= News: Silver Legion Rally

The Silver Legion has staged its largest rally yet. Pelley speaks beneath banners and floodlights, promising to cleanse the republic of bankers, socialists, immigrants, and traitors.

The numbers are still smaller than the headlines imply. The danger is that spectacle can make a minority look inevitable.

- @veterans_counterrally: Organize a democratic veterans counter-rally.
- @deny_permits: Push cities to deny permits.
- @monitor_only: Monitor them and avoid a martyrdom story.

@veterans_counterrally
title: Organize a democratic veterans counter-rally.
subtitle: Requires some defense organization.
choose-if: rb_strength >= 150
unavailable-subtitle: Democratic defense groups are not organized enough.
on-arrival: rb_strength += 60; pro_republic += 3; workers_nsdap -= 2 if workers_nsdap > 2; unemployed_nsdap -= 2 if unemployed_nsdap > 2; coup_progress -= 1 if coup_progress > 0

Veterans, union stewards, church groups, and local Democrats fill the streets without copying the Legion's politics.

@deny_permits
title: Push cities to deny permits.
subtitle: Slows the rally circuit; civil-liberties criticism rises.
on-arrival: sa_strength -= 80 if sa_strength >= 80; sa_militancy += 0.02; kpd_relation -= 2; ddp_relation -= 2; constitutional_stress += 1

Mayors and police chiefs find every procedural reason to block the next rallies. It works, but not cleanly.

@monitor_only
title: Monitor them and avoid a martyrdom story.
subtitle: Saves political capital; organization continues.
on-arrival: sa_strength += 80; radio_reach += 1; coup_progress += 1

Federal investigators watch, collect names, and wait. The Legion keeps marching.
